<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Shrill-tongued" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Shrill-tongued,</orth> 1) having a loud and resounding voice: <cit><quote>s. tapsters,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 849" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 849</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>when s. Fulvia scolds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 1.1.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. I, 1, 32</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) speaking in a high tone: <cit><quote>is she s. or low?</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 3.3.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 3, 15</bibl></cit>.
